Azure Storage Services provide scalable, durable, and secure storage solutions for different types of data.

Key services include:

* Blob Storage (unstructured data)
* File Storage (shared file systems)
* Queue Storage (message queues)
* Table Storage (NoSQL structured data)

For example, an application can store images in Blob Storage and logs in Table Storage.

A real-life use case is an e-commerce platform storing product images and customer data.

Another example is IoT systems storing sensor data.

Azure Storage ensures high availability and durability.
